85.3	Richmond,_Virginia	Richmond, Virginia	Richmond ( ) is the capital of the Commonwealth of Virginia, in the United States. It is an independent city and not part of any county. Richmond is the center of the Richmond Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA) and the Greater Richmond area. The population within the city limits was 204,214 in 2010, with an estimated population of 1,258,251 for the Richmond Metropolitan Area â€” making it the third largest in Virginia.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Collage_of_Landmarks_in_Richmond%2C_Virginia_v_1.jpg/300px-Collage_of_Landmarks_in_Richmond%2C_Virginia_v_1.jpg
